  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Comprehensive federal regulations\n- Strong emphasis on reporting requirements\n- Strict criminal and civil penalties\n- Robust asset forfeiture mechanisms\n\n2. European Union\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Harmonized regulatory framework\n- Risk-based supervision approach\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Cross-border cooperation mechanisms\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence infrastructure\n- Strict Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Extensive international collaboration\n- Complex beneficial ownership disclosure rules\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Historically lenient banking secrecy laws\n- Gradually strengthening anti-money laundering regulations\n- Enhanced international transparency requirements\n- Sophisticated financial monitoring systems\n\n5. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Strict capital control mechanisms\n- Growing emphasis on international compliance\n- Significant criminal penalties\n\n6. Singapore\n- Comprehensive regulatory framework\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n- Strict enforcement\n- Proactive international cooperation\n\nKey comparative observations:\n- Increasing global regulatory convergence\n- Growing technological integration\n- Heightened international collaboration\n- Risk-based regulatory approaches\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of these approaches?",
